Boil @water{600%ml} in a #pot with the @chicken stock pot{1}. Peel and finely chop the @onion{1} and roughly chop the @flat leaf parsley{5}. Peel and chop the @garlic cloves{2}(peeled and chopped). Remove the core from the @green pepper{2}, cut into 1cm strips then chop into small cubes. Zest the @orange{1} and finally, cut the @British chicken thighs{6} into bite-sized pieces.

Heat @olive oil{2%tbsp} in a #nonstick frying pan on high heat. Cook the chicken with a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{} until browned off on all sides. Add the orange zest and then pour in the @honey{1}. Toss for ~{1%minute} before removing from the pan and keeping to one side.

Lower the heat to medium and add @olive oil{4%tbsp}. Add the onion and cook for ~{2-3%minutes}. Add the @chorizo{2}(diced) to the pan with the garlic and green pepper. Cook for another ~{5%minutes}.

Add in the @basmati rice{2} and the @chopped tomatoes{2} together with the 600ml of chicken stock. Place a #lid on the pan and cook on medium-low heat for ~{10%minutes}. Add back the chicken with the juice of a quarter of the orange and a few shakes of @habanero sauce{1}. Cook for another ~{10%minutes} with the lid off and then taste a bit of your rice to check it's cooked and seasoned enough.

Once your rice is perfectly cooked, stir in the chopped parsley and a final squeeze of orange juice. If you want more heat add a few more shakes of the habanero sauce!

> Habanero sauce is the secret ingredient for that perfect cajun kick - add as little or as much as you like, depending on how much you want to spice things up.